g.text: - solution is ORIG, PCA or RECENT
- build() : solve for the kernel if not cached
- Direct access to kernel within the solution
- Can be spatially varying or non-varying.
- parameters (coefficients): fixed (numbers) or spatially varying (2D functions)
- Kernel image can be calculated at any (x,y) position
- Spatially dependent coefficients cannot be directly computed by python call.
- Last parameter values can be obtained.
- Spatial functions can be obtained and evaluated separately.
